abstract: >
  Games.Hispanistica is an open-source, higher-education teaching project that
  develops interactive, game-based learning modules for Spanish linguistics.
  The project emerges from university teaching and is closely connected to the
  digital textbook "Spanische Linguistik @ School". Its primary aim is to
  support active learning by complementing textual explanations with
  interactive formats that foster repetition, application, and reflection.

  The games are developed collaboratively in teaching contexts, with students
  participating in the conceptual design of content, game mechanics, and task
  structures. Technical implementation follows didactic decisions and enables
  the realization of custom, non-template-based games using open-source
  technologies. Generative AI is employed primarily as a development and
  implementation aid, supporting the translation of didactic concepts into
  modular, reusable code.

  Games.Hispanistica is designed as an open and evolving infrastructure that
  supports reuse, adaptation, and further development in other linguistic or
  educational contexts.

